NATION BRIEFS
																																												 New Delhi, Dec. 7 (PTI): The government has turned down the recommendation of the law commission to set up a panel on withdrawal of life support system from terminally ill patients, law minister H.R. Bhardwaj told the Lok Sabha today. Every competent patient, who is suffering from terminal illness, has a right to refuse medical treatment, the commission had said.
																																												Bangalore (PTI): A Sri Lankan national trying to fly out to London with a forged Spanish passport has been detained at the airport. The man, identified as Vigneshwaran, was taken into custody on Thursday after immigration check. 
																																												Kannur (PTI): A Congress general secretary in Kerala, K. Sudhakaran, on Friday shared the stage with BJP leader Rajiv Pratap Rudy to attack the CPM. Sudhakaran told the meeting organised by a pro-BJP group he was not afraid of using the platform of any party to oppose the ruling CPM.
																																												New York (PTI): A civil liberties group has filed a case against New York police on behalf of an Indian-origin student who was allegedly unlawfully handcuffed and detained for about half an hour in July for taking pictures of a subway station.

